SUPER Eagles midfielder Wilfred Ndidi has said that the team will approach Sunday’s Last-16 encounter against Carthage Eagles of Tunisia with the same winning mentality. Nigeria qualified for the Round of 16 with a 100 percent record, winning all their group matches to set up a clash with the Carthage Eagles that managed a win in their group games. The Leicester City star stressed that the players are focused and prepared for the Tunisia clash.   Qatar 2022: Nigeria face Ghana in play-off clash     COVID 19: Keeper crisis hits Comoros against Cameroon     COVID-19 rules Tunisia coach, 12 players out of Eagles tie   “This is the reason why we are here. We are here to compete and try as much as we can to go far in the tournament. We are playing a new team with a different approach with the same mentality,” Ndidi said. - Advertisement - The 25-year-old player said the new head coach Augustine Eguavoen has instilled confidence in the team. “The 2019 team and the present team are the same but with a different philosophy. Our new coach has told us to make things simple and told us to believe in ourselves. He gave us a push to express ourselves and have freedom. He also told us that if you have the freedom you have to play for the team and that is the difference between this team and the 2019 team,” he added.